./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:7:1. `spec.md` is no longer implementation-safe because its summary, handoff criteria, scope, and requirements still assume reducer-local ownership, nested `findings[]` extractor inputs, and custom `Findings` / `Citations` columns. The rewrite target is a workflow-owned `phase_synthesis` emission step that consumes delta JSONL streams and renders the existing `Path | Action | Status | Note` template without adding columns. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:4] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:50] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:78] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:135] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:67] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:827] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_confirm.yaml:999] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/resource-map.md:37] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/resource-map.md:67]
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:8:2. The packet task plan is pointed at the wrong implementation seam. `T013`-`T018` still wire reducers and generic YAML edits, but the live contract requires top-level `resourceMap.emit` config plumbing, `--no-resource-map` command parsing, `state_paths.resource_map_output`, and a dedicated `step_emit_resource_map` inserted in synthesis after summary hydration and, in confirm mode, after the pre-synthesis gate but before narrative compilation. `T025`-`T028` should stop creating new wildcard docs and instead edit the existing synthesis feature-catalog and finalization playbook files already used as the operator-facing contract. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:58] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:61] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:63] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:73] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-research.md:64] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-review.md:62] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:831] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_confirm.yaml:975] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:26]
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:9:3. The verification checklist still encodes the stale behavior model. `CHK-011` should verify synthesis-step ordering instead of reducer-write races, `CHK-020`-`CHK-025` should verify Note/Summary-based counts plus the hard-failure boundary for missing canonical iteration artifacts, and `CHK-040`-`CHK-045` should cover the existing command, synthesis feature, and final-synthesis playbook surfaces rather than implying new standalone docs or template forks. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/checklist.md:55] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/checklist.md:66] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/checklist.md:69] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/checklist.md:89] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/resource-map.md:39] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/resource-map.md:45] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:50] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:788] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/019-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:26] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:26]
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:10:4. The file/change inventory in the packet is still too “new-surface” heavy for the live contract. The rewrite list should keep the shared extractor and command docs, add both config templates as explicit edit targets, keep the four YAML workflows as synthesis-step edits, and replace wildcard “create feature/playbook docs” language with edits to `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md`, and the two final-synthesis playbook scenarios that currently only mention `research/research.md` or `review/review-report.md`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:100] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:118] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-research.md:183] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-review.md:204] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:25] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/019-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:31] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:31]
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/iterations/iteration-005.md:14:- Preserving the packet's wildcard “create new feature/playbook entry” approach as the primary docs plan. The live operator-facing synthesis contract already lives in the existing synthesis pages and finalization scenarios, so leaving those unchanged would keep the canonical docs stale. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-resource-map-template/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:73] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:66]
