./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/research.md:52:- The opt-out/config plumbing is now concrete: add a top-level `resourceMap.emit` boolean to both deep-loop config templates, default it to `true`, and map `--no-resource-map` in the command setup flow directly onto that field. The current config templates have no `resourceMap` block, and `parseExecutorConfig()` only validates the `executor` subtree, so this should not be wired into executor config. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-research.md:64] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-review.md:62] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json:1] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json:1] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts:21]
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/research.md:53:- The extractor boundary should be file/stream-based, not packet-prose-shaped: collect evidence from `deltas/iter-*.jsonl`, normalize the event rows into template rows plus summary metadata, then render markdown. Review severities and research citation totals belong in `Note` text and Summary counts because the phase-012 template only provides `Path | Action | Status | Note`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:108] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:307] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/resource-map.md:39] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/resource-map.md:67]
