./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-dashboard.md:70:- Treating prompt-pack JSON examples as the sole authoritative schema. They are necessary for dispatch validation, but insufficient for downstream aggregation because the reducer and review-mode contracts consume richer fields and lineage state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:308] (iteration 1)
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-dashboard.md:71:- Using the packet spec's proposed `findings[]` delta shape as the implementation baseline. The shipped delta format is line-oriented event JSONL, so direct extractor input from packet prose would be misleading. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:78] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:50] (iteration 1)
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-dashboard.md:74:- Reducer-local ownership as the primary emission point. Reducers currently guarantee synchronized registry/strategy/dashboard refreshes only; adding convergence-only artifact emission there would widen reducer scope and make every refresh path responsible for template rendering. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:748] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1128] (iteration 2)
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-dashboard.md:76:- Re-resolving artifact roots inside the emitter or extractor. Child-phase packet allocation is not stable across repeated fresh resolves, so the emitter must inherit the already-resolved `{artifact_dir}` from workflow state instead. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs:31] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs:117] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:823] (iteration 3)
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-dashboard.md:77:- Treating the packet's current file list as "new standalone feature/playbook docs everywhere" without first updating the existing synthesis docs. The shipped synthesis feature files and finalization playbooks are already the authoritative contract surface, so ignoring them would leave the main operator-facing sources stale even if new helper docs were added. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:31] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/019-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:60] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:60] (iteration 3)
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-dashboard.md:80:- Treating the extractor input as the packet's current `findings[]`-style pseudo-schema. The live deltas are line-oriented event streams, so any implementation that skips a normalization stage will drift from real workflow data immediately. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:50] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:78] (iteration 4)
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-dashboard.md:82:- Preserving the packet's wildcard “create new feature/playbook entry” approach as the primary docs plan. The live operator-facing synthesis contract already lives in the existing synthesis pages and finalization scenarios, so leaving those unchanged would keep the canonical docs stale. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:73] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:66] (iteration 5)
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:12:      "text": "What are the real reducer inputs and per-iteration evidence shapes in sk-deep-review and sk-deep-research today, and what normalization is actually required?",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:44:      "text": "The live delta contract is event-stream JSONL, not a nested per-iteration array payload. Deep research delta files are documented as one `type:\"iteration\"` row plus one row per `graphEvent`, `finding`, `invariant`, `observation`, `edge`, and `ruled_out`; deep review uses one row per `graphEvent`, `finding`, `classification`, `traceability-check`, and `ruled_out`. Phase 013's current spec assumes an extractor input like `review deltas (with findings[])` and `research deltas (with source_paths[] / citations[])`, which is already underspecified against the shipped stream format and therefore needs an adapter layer before any shared extractor can exist. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:50] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:75] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:78]",
