./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:67:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:67",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:68:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:308",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:69:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1136"
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:74:      "text": "The reducer boundary already owns synchronized derived outputs and sits after strict post-dispatch artifact validation. The deep research workflow validates the iteration markdown, the state-log append, and the per-iteration delta file before it runs `reduce-state.cjs`; the reducer then reads config, state log, strategy, and iteration files and rewrites registry, strategy, and dashboard. That makes the safest low-coupling emission point a convergence-aware step adjacent to or immediately after reducer execution, not inside the leaf-agent contract and not as a per-iteration side effect. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:724] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:823] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1136]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:79:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:80:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:823",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:82:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:67",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:83:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:308",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:84:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1136"
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:89:      "text": "The shipped iteration prompt packs define a minimal canonical append contract, but the live reducers and review-mode contract still depend on richer run-based records. Deep research dispatch tells the agent to append only `type`, `iteration`, `newInfoRatio`, `status`, and `focus`, while the reducer dashboard renders `record.run` and `record.findingsCount`; deep review likewise advertises a minimal `iteration` schema in the prompt pack, but the review-mode contract requires `mode`, `run`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, lineage fields, and timestamps. This means phase 013 cannot treat the prompt-pack JSON example as the whole truth and should normalize from richer evidence streams or reducer-normalized state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:699] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:67] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:308]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:94:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:95:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:823",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:97:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:67",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:98:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:308",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:99:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1136"
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:104:      "text": "Reducers are intentionally scoped to synchronized derived state, not convergence-only authored artifacts. The research reducer reads config/state/strategy/iterations, derives registry + strategy + dashboard, and writes only those three outputs; the review reducer does the same for review registry + strategy + dashboard, and both reducers explicitly promise idempotence for identical inputs. Putting `resource-map.md` generation inside reducers would mix template rendering and convergence-time file policy into a component that currently just refreshes deterministic state views. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:855] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:872] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1128] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1179]",
