./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:207:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:593",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:214:      "text": "The lowest-coupling doc/test updates are anchored to existing synthesis surfaces, and the packet's wildcard \"create a new resource-map-emission file everywhere\" list is too coarse. Both command entrypoints, both SKILL.md files, both existing synthesis feature-catalog files, and the final-synthesis manual playbooks currently describe only `research.md` or `review-report.md` as terminal artifacts. Those existing files are the authoritative places to extend the synthesis contract. In addition, both playbook suites still contain stale notes claiming no dedicated feature catalog exists even though `feature_catalog/` is present for both skills, so the doc update set needs to fix that drift as part of phase 013. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-research.md:183] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-review.md:194] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/SKILL.md:287] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/SKILL.md:295] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:25] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/019-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:67] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:67] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:593]",
