./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:282:      "text": "The packet's opt-out/config wording needs revision to match the live config style and workflow ownership split. The live deep-research config schema is camelCase and treats `{artifact_dir}` packet files as workflow-owned outputs, while the phase-013 packet currently specifies reducer-local emission plus a snake_case `config.resource_map.emit` field. The implementation contract should instead add a workflow-owned config field consistent with the existing JSON schema naming, then document the CLI flag and synthesis-step skip behavior across command + skill surfaces. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/state_format.md:17] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/state_format.md:25] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/state_format.md:45] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:81] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:83] [INFERENCE: the production config field should follow the existing camelCase config schema rather than introduce a one-off snake_case branch.]",
