./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:343:        ".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:593",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:350:      "text": "Phase 013 packet docs now need a focused rewrite away from reducer-local hooks and template forks. The current spec still says reducers call the extractor and that emitted maps gain custom `Findings` or `Citations` columns; the task list still schedules reducer-branch wiring plus creation of new feature/playbook files; the checklist still verifies custom-column behavior and those new docs. Live evidence says the packet should instead point to a workflow-owned `step_emit_resource_map` in `phase_synthesis`, a shared delta-file extractor/renderer, updates to the existing synthesis feature-catalog pages, and updates to the existing final-synthesis playbooks. Concretely: rewrite spec scope/requirements/files-to-change in [spec.md] to reference `state_paths.resource_map_output` and `Note`-column counts; rewrite T013-T018 around synthesis-time workflow plumbing; replace T025-T028 with edits to the current synthesis feature/playbook files; and align checklist items to verify template-faithful `Note` text, synthesis-surface docs, and opt-out behavior. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:78] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:135] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:58] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:73] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/checklist.md:55] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/checklist.md:89] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:24]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:358:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json:1`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:359:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json:1`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:361:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:362:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:307`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:367:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:18`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:368:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:24`"
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:373:      "text": "The clean opt-out path is a new top-level `resourceMap.emit` boolean in both deep-loop config templates, defaulting to `true`, with `--no-resource-map` mapped in the command setup flow directly onto that field. Both command entrypoints already describe CLI-flag-to-config mapping for non-executor settings, both config templates currently lack any `resourceMap` block, and `parseExecutorConfig()` only validates the `executor` subtree, so pushing the flag into `executor-config.ts` would be the wrong coupling point. The workflow delta is: add `resourceMap.emit` to `assets/deep_research_config.json` and `assets/deep_review_config.json`, teach `/spec_kit:deep-research` and `/spec_kit:deep-review` to parse `--no-resource-map`, and guard a new synthesis-time `step_emit_resource_map` with `config.resourceMap.emit != false`. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-research.md:64] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-review.md:62] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json:1] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json:1] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts:21] [INFERENCE: the existing flag-mapping pattern and executor-only validator make a top-level `resourceMap` config block the lowest-coupling place to wire an opt-out flag.]",
