./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:780:      "text": "Emitting from the leaf agent or per-iteration prompt contract. Post-dispatch validation and reducer synchronization already define the stable workflow boundary, so pushing resource-map generation into the agent would increase coupling to executor/prompt drift. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:724] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1171]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:785:      "text": "Treating prompt-pack JSON examples as the sole authoritative schema. They are necessary for dispatch validation, but insufficient for downstream aggregation because the reducer and review-mode contracts consume richer fields and lineage state. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:308]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:790:      "text": "Using the packet spec's proposed `findings[]` delta shape as the implementation baseline. The shipped delta format is line-oriented event JSONL, so direct extractor input from packet prose would be misleading. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:78] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:50]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:805:      "text": "Reducer-local ownership as the primary emission point. Reducers currently guarantee synchronized registry/strategy/dashboard refreshes only; adding convergence-only artifact emission there would widen reducer scope and make every refresh path responsible for template rendering. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:748] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1128]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:815:      "text": "Re-resolving artifact roots inside the emitter or extractor. Child-phase packet allocation is not stable across repeated fresh resolves, so the emitter must inherit the already-resolved `{artifact_dir}` from workflow state instead. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs:31] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs:117] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:823]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:820:      "text": "Treating the packet's current file list as \"new standalone feature/playbook docs everywhere\" without first updating the existing synthesis docs. The shipped synthesis feature files and finalization playbooks are already the authoritative contract surface, so ignoring them would leave the main operator-facing sources stale even if new helper docs were added. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:31] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/019-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:60] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:60]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:835:      "text": "Treating the extractor input as the packet's current `findings[]`-style pseudo-schema. The live deltas are line-oriented event streams, so any implementation that skips a normalization stage will drift from real workflow data immediately. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:50] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/spec.md:78]",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/findings-registry.json:845:      "text": "Preserving the packet's wildcard “create new feature/playbook entry” approach as the primary docs plan. The live operator-facing synthesis contract already lives in the existing synthesis pages and finalization scenarios, so leaving those unchanged would keep the canonical docs stale. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/tasks.md:73] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/feature_catalog/01--loop-lifecycle/04-synthesis.md:18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/manual_testing_playbook/06--synthesis-save-and-guardrails/027-final-synthesis-memory-save-and-guardrail-behavior.md:66]",
