./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-state.jsonl:1:{"type":"config","topic":"Deeply investigate what needs to be implemented for packet 026/013 to integrate automatic convergence-time resource-map.md emission into sk-deep-review and sk-deep-research in a smart, low-coupling way. Determine the live delta/state schemas, safest integration points, template-fit constraints, workflow/docs/test changes, and the edge-case handling needed for a production-quality implementation.","maxIterations":7,"convergenceThreshold":0.05,"createdAt":"2026-04-24T10:30:43.408Z","specFolder":"system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration"}
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-state.jsonl:2:{"type":"iteration","iteration":1,"run":1,"status":"complete","focus":"Validate the live deep-loop data contracts first: inspect real reducer inputs, JSONL records, and delta expectations in both sk-deep-review and sk-deep-research so the resource-map design is grounded in shipped shapes rather than packet assumptions.","findingsCount":4,"newInfoRatio":1,"noveltyJustification":"All 4 findings were newly established from shipped reducer, workflow, and template contracts, including two packet-spec drift points.","keyQuestions":["What are the real reducer inputs and per-iteration evidence shapes in sk-deep-review and sk-deep-research today, and what normalization is actually required?","What is the smartest minimal-coupling integration point for resource-map emission: inside the reducers, as a post-reducer workflow step, or during synthesis?","How should the emitted review and research maps extend the phase-012 resource-map template without creating format drift or brittle template coupling?"],"answeredQuestions":["What are the real reducer inputs and per-iteration evidence shapes in sk-deep-review and sk-deep-research today, and what normalization is actually required?"],"ruledOut":["Use the packet spec's nested findings[] delta shape as the live baseline","Emit resource-map generation from the leaf agent contract"],"toolsUsed":["Read","Grep"],"sourcesQueried":[".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl:40",".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:823",".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml:308",".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/resource-map.md:21"],"timestamp":"2026-04-24T10:31:16+02:00","durationMs":420000}
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-state.jsonl:3:{"type":"iteration","iteration":2,"run":2,"status":"complete","focus":"Trace the live convergence/finalization path in both deep-loop workflows and reducers: determine whether resource-map emission should run inside reducer finalization, in a dedicated post-reducer workflow step, or alongside synthesis/report generation, and catalog the docs/tests/YAML surfaces that already describe that boundary.","findingsCount":4,"newInfoRatio":0.75,"noveltyJustification":"2 of 4 findings were new and 2 refined prior reducer-adjacent conclusions into an exact workflow ownership boundary and concrete surface list.","keyQuestions":["What is the smartest minimal-coupling integration point for resource-map emission: inside the reducers, as a post-reducer workflow step, or during synthesis?","Which command, YAML, docs, catalog, playbook, and test surfaces must change to satisfy the phase-013 acceptance criteria end-to-end?"],"answeredQuestions":["What is the smartest minimal-coupling integration point for resource-map emission: inside the reducers, as a post-reducer workflow step, or during synthesis?"],"ruledOut":["Reducer-local resource-map emission as the primary ownership point","Embedding resource-map generation inside narrative synthesis/report compilation"],"toolsUsed":["Read","Grep"],"sourcesQueried":[".opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:748",".opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:827",".opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:760",".opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:873",".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:855",".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:1128",".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/state_format.md:15",".opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/loop_protocol.md:150"],"focusTrack":"integration-boundary","timestamp":"2026-04-24T12:37:16+02:00","durationMs":540000}
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-resource-map-deep-loop-fix/003-resource-map-deep-loop-integration/research/deep-research-state.jsonl:4:{"type":"iteration","iteration":3,"run":3,"status":"complete","focus":"Pin the exact implementation contract for a workflow-owned emitter step at `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md`, then map the required auto/confirm YAML, command/docs, playbook/catalog, and edge-case updates.","findingsCount":5,"newInfoRatio":0.9,"noveltyJustification":"4 findings were newly established and 1 refined the earlier ownership decision into concrete packet/doc drift corrections.","keyQuestions":["How should the emitted review and research maps extend the phase-012 resource-map template without creating format drift or brittle template coupling?","Which command, YAML, docs, catalog, playbook, and test surfaces must change to satisfy the phase-013 acceptance criteria end-to-end?","Which failure modes and edge cases need explicit handling so the feature is idempotent, child-phase-safe, and resilient to malformed or partial evidence?"],"answeredQuestions":["How should the emitted review and research maps extend the phase-012 resource-map template without creating format drift or brittle template coupling?","Which command, YAML, docs, catalog, playbook, and test surfaces must change to satisfy the phase-013 acceptance criteria end-to-end?"],"ruledOut":["Add custom review/research signal columns to the resource-map tables","Re-resolve artifact roots inside the convergence emitter"],"toolsUsed":["Read","Grep"],"sourcesQueried":[".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/resource-map.md:39",".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs:77",".opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:780",".opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_confirm.yaml:975",".opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-research.md:183",".opencode/commands/spec_kit/deep-review.md:194",".opencode/skills/