./.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/060-sk-agent-improver-test-report-alignment/spec.md:159:- **Cross-architecture validation** (added 2026-05-03 from 062 follow-on) — the 060/004 methodology was empirically applied to two more same-architecture LEAF agents in packet `../062-deep-loop-command-flow-stress-tests/`. Result: `@deep-research` PASS 6/0/0 R1 clean (clean-substrate confirmation); `@deep-review` PASS 0/5/1 across R1+R2 (real discipline gaps surfaced — setup-binding emission, refusal-discipline wording). The asymmetric outcome is the methodology working as designed: it correctly distinguishes well-disciplined agents from those with hidden gaps. Recommendations applied to sk-deep-review SKILL.md ALWAYS rules 13+14 (BINDING + REFUSE canonical wording) close the surfaced gaps; expected R3 ≈ PASS 5+/PARTIAL 0-1.
