./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-continuity-memory-runtime/003-continuity-refactor-gates/prompts/research-prompt-implementation.md:5:> **Target runtime**: `cli-codex gpt-5.4 high fast` — either as a single-shot delegation piped via stdin, or as input to `/spec_kit:deep-research:auto`. This prompt follows the `sk-deep-research v1.5.0` strategy template format.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-continuity-memory-runtime/003-continuity-refactor-gates/prompts/research-prompt-implementation.md:15:> **⚠ MANDATORY**: This prompt **MUST** be driven by `/spec_kit:deep-research:auto` (or `:confirm`). It is **not** designed to run as a single-shot Codex brief, and a single-shot run would bypass the entire sk-deep-research loop driver — producing an incomplete, unauditable research packet.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-continuity-memory-runtime/003-continuity-refactor-gates/prompts/research-prompt-implementation.md:17:> The sk-deep-research loop is what creates the required state files:
