./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/003-continuity-memory-runtime/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:37:- `FIND-iter002-reducer-derived-overwrite` | Severity: `P2` | File:line: `.claude/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:23-26`, `.claude/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:823-875` | Description: reducer-owned outputs (`findings-registry.json`, `deep-research-strategy.md`, `deep-research-dashboard.md`) are plain `writeFileSync()` overwrites with no temp-file promotion and no reducer lock. | Repro / observed behavior: concurrent reducer invocations both read the same JSONL, derive state, and then the last `writeUtf8(...)` wins for all three files. | Why it matters: JSONL remains the source of truth, but live steering artifacts can jump backward or flicker until recomputed, which degrades observability rather than corrupting canonical evidence.
