./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7068:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:34:- What worked and why: Comparing live reducer imports and search hits against the documented bridge contract made the missing runtime handoff explicit very quickly.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7069:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:35:- What did not work and why: Repo-wide symbol search still surfaced older packet/spec artifacts, so I had to keep separating "promised by 042 docs" from "called by active runtime code."
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7070:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-003.md:39:Rotate to D4 and verify whether the documented lineage modes and stop-state persistence are actually exercised by the live workflows: compare the deep-research/deep-review YAMLs, reducer inputs, and JSONL event handling to see whether `resume`, `restart`, `fork`, `completed-continue`, and `blockedStop` with full gate payloads survive the normal runtime path or remain primarily contractual/documented behavior.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7147:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:4:This iteration rotated to D4 and audited whether the shipped reducers for `sk-deep-research`, `sk-deep-review`, and `sk-improve-agent` write outside their declared machine-owned zones. The scope was limited to reducer write paths, target markdown/state assets, and the published ownership contracts for strategy, dashboard, registry, and report surfaces.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7148:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:7:- `sk-deep-research` is anchor-scoped and fail-closed on strategy writes. Its reducer only replaces the `key-questions`, `answered-questions`, `what-worked`, `what-failed`, `exhausted-approaches`, `ruled-out-directions`, and `next-focus` anchor blocks, and it throws if any requested anchor is missing; that matches the research strategy contract declaring sections 3 and 6-11 reducer-rewritten while leaving sections 1, 2, 4, 5, 12, and 13 stable (`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:20-21`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:317-331`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:353-366`).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7149:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:8:- The same `sk-deep-research` reducer only writes three outputs in its normal pass: `findings-registry.json`, `deep-research-strategy.md`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`. I found no reducer path that touches iteration markdown or any other human-authored research asset during refresh (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:478-507`).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7150:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:11:- `sk-deep-review` is fail-open where `sk-deep-research` is fail-closed: if an expected anchor is missing, `replaceAnchorSection()` returns the original content instead of halting, and the reducer still writes the resulting strategy file back out. That prevents cross-anchor spill into adjacent human-owned sections, but it also means corrupted or missing machine-owned zones can silently persist (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:431-445`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:640-645`).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7151:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:22:- `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:20-21`
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7152:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:23:- `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:317-366`
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7153:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:24:- `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:478-507`
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7154:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:41:Rotate to D5 and inspect the live convergence math plus its callers to determine whether the coverage graph contributes materially to stop gating or only decorates already ratio-driven decisions. The most productive next pass is to trace the research/review convergence helpers and any YAML/runtime call sites that pass graph-derived signals, then compare the documented graph-aware stop language against the actual weight each graph-backed signal carries in the final composite and blocking decisions.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7178:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:1:# Iteration 7: D1 Research Convergence Signal Gap Audit
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7179:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:4:This iteration stayed on D1 and compared the live deep-research stop path against the richer research-signal set already implemented in the shared coverage-graph stack. The goal was to separate concrete runtime gaps from signals that look intentionally not adopted by the current deep-research contract.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7180:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:7:- The live deep-research workflow still evaluates STOP with a local 3-signal vote only: rolling average, MAD noise floor, and question entropy, then falls through a generic `checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)` call. The active convergence step does not name `contradictionDensity`, `sourceDiversity`, `claimVerificationRate`, or `evidenceDepth` anywhere in the runtime algorithm (.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:250-277).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7181:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:8:- `sourceDiversity` is not a speculative extra from the shared graph stack; the deep-research convergence contract already makes it a first-class `qualityGate.checks` sub-check inside the legal-stop bundle. That means the current lack of an explicit shared-graph bridge for this signal is a runtime integration gap, not a deliberate omission (.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:214-220; .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:246-260; .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:297-303).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7182:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:9:- `contradictionDensity` is also already part of the published deep-research convergence model: the contract says high contradiction density should block STOP and surface as a `qualityGate` semantic sub-check. Because the live workflow's active stop math still stops at the inline 3-signal vote, this is another concrete runtime gap rather than a merely hypothetical graph enhancement (.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:363-386; .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:411-423; .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:250-277).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7183:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:10:- The shared coverage-graph stack already computes a richer research convergence payload with `questionCoverage`, `claimVerificationRate`, `contradictionDensity`, `sourceDiversity`, and `evidenceDepth`, then evaluates `sourceDiversity` and `evidenceDepth` as blocking guards and escalates high contradiction density or unverified claims into blockers/warnings. So the infrastructure gap is not in the graph/MCP layer; it is in the deep-research runtime not calling that layer (.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:35-41; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:163-228; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:175-275).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7184:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:11:- `claimVerificationRate` and `evidenceDepth` look like deliberate non-adoptions in `sk-deep-research` rather than current regressions. The shared graph stack exposes both signals, but the published deep-research semantic extension still names `semanticNovelty`, `contradictionDensity`, and `citationOverlap` as the added semantic checks, not claim-verification or path-depth gates (.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:35-41; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:163-228; .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:341-457).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7185:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:12:- The reducer still cannot surface graph-backed research convergence even when `graphEvents` are present. It derives its convergence score from `latestIteration.convergenceSignals?.compositeStop ?? latestIteration?.newInfoRatio`, while the same convergence reference says the reducer should derive additional graph signals when `graphEvents` exist. That leaves graph-side research signals operationally disconnected from packet-level status surfaces (.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:244-249; .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:1181-1205).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7186:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-007.md:15:- This is not primarily a shared-infrastructure deficit: the graph/MCP layer already computes and evaluates the richer research signals, including blocker semantics for `sourceDiversity`, `evidenceDepth`, contradictions, and unverified claims (.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:163-228; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:175-275).
