./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7688:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:184:        ".opencode/agents/deep-research.md:159-166"
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:7689:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:189:      "text": "Contradiction handling is split across layers: the CJS helper can scan in-memory `CONTRADICTS` edges, but the active convergence handler actually blocks on contradictions through the TypeScript query layer (`findContradictions(ns)`), which implies graph-aware contradiction blocking depends on a populated persisted namespace rather than on raw JSONL `graphEvents` alone (.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/coverage-graph-contradictions.cjs:37-67; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/coverage-graph-contradictions.cjs:85-129; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:20-25; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:255-257; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:353-355).",
