./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8043:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1461:        "`.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:322-331`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8044:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1467:      "text": "The \"live\" graph convergence path exists, but as a separate MCP decision engine rather than the reducer math the loops visibly consume here. The handler computes research/review thresholds, classifies signals as `weighted` vs `blocking_guard`, and can return `STOP_ALLOWED` only \"pending newInfoRatio agreement.\" That means graph convergence is architecturally downstream-compatible with loop stop logic, but still not the same thing as the reducer's current `compositeStop` pass-through (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:58-118`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:183-239`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:290-379`).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8045:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1470:        "`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:48-52`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8046:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1471:        "`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:38-39`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8047:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1476:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:244-273`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8048:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1477:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:438-443`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8049:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1480:        "`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:1183-1205`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8050:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1482:        "`.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:322-331`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8051:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1488:      "text": "The published convergence docs currently overstate reducer-side graph usage. Research docs say the reducer builds an in-memory graph from `graphEvents` and adds a `graphCoverage` sub-check to legal-stop evaluation; review docs make the same claim for `graphEvidence` under `findingStability`. But the workflow path I traced tells the LEAF agent to emit optional `graphEvents` and then runs `reduce-state.cjs`, while the inspected reducers themselves do not implement the documented graph rebuild or extra gate expansion (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:1183-1205`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/convergence.md:661-683`, `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:322-331`, `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:432-437`).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8052:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1491:        "`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md:48-52`",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8053:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1492:        "`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-013.md:38-39`",
