./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8258:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2393:      "text": ".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:7-10",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8259:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2397:      "id": "ruled-out-3-12-no-hidden-bridge-appeared-in-the-active-reducer-path-the-deep-research-reducer-s",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8260:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2398:      "text": "No hidden bridge appeared in the active reducer path: the deep-research reducer still has no MCP/tool client imports and no graph-event parsing branch, so the bridge is not merely buried deeper in the same file (.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:11-12; .opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:246-247).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8261:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2412:      "id": "ruled-out-4-3-this-is-not-isolated-to-one-loop-the-research-and-review-auto-yamls-both-classif",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8262:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2413:      "text": "This is not isolated to one loop. The research and review auto YAMLs both classify the same lineage branches while only surfacing a smaller event set in the active runtime path (`.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:128-153`, `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:155-177`).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8263:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2418:      "text": "This is not just a documentation omission. Both convergence references are explicit about first-class blocked-stop persistence and full gate bundles, so the drift is between published contract and live workflow serialization, not between two equally vague docs (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:305-309`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/convergence.md:58-85`).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8264:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2433:      "text": "This is not a documentation-gap false alarm: both convergence references already define the shared enum, the legacy-label normalization rules, and the required blocked-stop persistence shape in detail (.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:21-31; .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/convergence.md:44-56).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8265:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2447:      "id": "ruled-out-6-3-this-is-not-limited-to-one-loop-both-research-and-review-convergence-references-",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8266:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2448:      "text": "This is not limited to one loop. Both research and review convergence references promise graph-aware gate participation, but both active auto workflows keep STOP evaluation inline and local (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:1181-1205`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/convergence.md:661-683`, `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml:250-277`, `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:343-375`).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8267:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2453:      "text": "`claimVerificationRate` and `evidenceDepth` should not yet be treated as contract drift in `sk-deep-research`; the current research convergence reference still frames the semantic extension around `semanticNovelty`, `contradictionDensity`, and `citationOverlap` instead (.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:341-457).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8268:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2458:      "text": "I did not inspect confirm-mode workflows in this pass because the question was whether the active deep-research runtime currently bridges to the shared graph signal set; the auto workflow, convergence reference, reducer, and shared graph handler were sufficient to classify the signal gaps.",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8269:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2463:      "text": "This is not primarily a shared-infrastructure deficit: the graph/MCP layer already computes and evaluates the richer research signals, including blocker semantics for `sourceDiversity`, `evidenceDepth`, contradictions, and unverified claims (.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:163-228; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:175-275).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8270:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2498:      "text": "This is not another reducer merge-stability regression. Iteration 9 already established that finding dedup and transition ordering stay stable at 50+ findings, which leaves observability and recovery handoff as the remaining D2 weakness (`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:7-11`).",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8271:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2517:      "id": "ruled-out-12-2-repo-wide-symbol-search-for-the-new-d3-modules-surfaced-mostly-docs-specs-change",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8272:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2518:      "text": "Repo-wide symbol search for the new D3 modules surfaced mostly docs, specs, changelog entries, and tests, which limited negative-proof evidence to the runtime files that do exist.",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8273:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2558:      "text": "A command-doc requirement to invoke structural graph tools before or during iterations; the inspected command surfaces only bootstrap CocoIndex.",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8274:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2562:      "id": "ruled-out-15-3-a-wrapper-level-deep-loop-graph-convergence-step-on-the-visible-research-review-",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8275:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2563:      "text": "A wrapper-level `deep_loop_graph_convergence` step on the visible research/review iteration path; the cited YAML paths go from iteration output to reducer execution without a graph-convergence call.",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8276:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2573:      "text": "I did not inspect hidden executor internals outside the published skill, workflow, and MCP handler surfaces, so the negative claim stays scoped to the shipped writer/validator/query path that is visible in-repo.",
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/003-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/002-scenario-execution/runs/I2/cli-codex-1/output.txt:8277:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2578:      "text": "The visible MCP coverage-graph path is not currently allowing `loop_type: \"improvement\"` to pollute shared research/review graphs; the stronger risk is documentation/strategy drift plus missing per-session read isolation inside the research/review namespaces.",
