e must survive both branches rather than only mutating the prompt file body.","Q-P2 evidence favors adding a non-mutating status readiness-action probe before lowering DEFAULT_DEBOUNCE_MS, because watcher tests already cover rapid saves, default-window coalescing, rename/delete cleanup, burst renames, concurrent renames, and symlink alias dedup.","code_graph_status currently calls getGraphFreshness and then emits readiness.action none, which hides selective_reindex/full_scan actions that detectState/ensureCodeGraphReady can already distinguish."],"timestamp":"2026-04-27T17:11:51Z"}
