./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/008-skill-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/review/review_archive/gen1-2026-04-13/iterations/iteration-007.md:16:- **F061**: Phase 004's CHK-014 evidence overstates what the packet actually serializes. The checklist says packet `graph-metadata.json` lists live repo files such as `sk-deep-review/graph-metadata.json` and `skill_graph_compiler.py`, but the current `derived.key_files` list only contains packet docs plus a subset of other skill metadata files; neither cited evidence file appears there. The packet did remove the old glob, but its claimed packet-metadata evidence surface is still inaccurate. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-search-routing-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/004-graph-metadata-enrichment/spec.md:79] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-search-routing-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/004-graph-metadata-enrichment/checklist.md:57] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-search-routing-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/004-graph-metadata-enrichment/graph-metadata.json:43] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-search-routing-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/004-graph-metadata-enrichment/graph-metadata.json:63]
