./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/008-skill-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/research/iterations/iteration-010.md:108:   - Review `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/graph-metadata.json:11-13`.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/008-skill-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:7:2. Only 2 of the 9 multi-skill phrase relationships in `PHRASE_INTENT_BOOSTERS` are now graph-backed. The redundant or partially redundant relationships are `spec folder review -> sk-code-review`, because `sk-deep-review` already `depends_on` `sk-code-review` at `0.8` (`.opencode/skills/skill-advisor/scripts/skill_advisor.py:707`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/graph-metadata.json:7-18`), and `figma css -> sk-code-web`, because `mcp-figma` already `enhances` `sk-code-web` at `0.4` (`.opencode/skills/skill-advisor/scripts/skill_advisor.py:716`, `.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/graph-metadata.json:7-18`). The remaining 7 multi-skill phrase relationships do not have graph equivalents yet: `pr review`, `merge readiness`, `ready to merge`, `api network`, `cross-ai review`, `codex review`, and `claude code review` (`.opencode/skills/skill-advisor/scripts/skill_advisor.py:616-638`, `.opencode/skills/skill-advisor/scripts/skill_advisor.py:728-750`).
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/008-skill-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:9:3. Even those 2 graph-backed relationships are not strong enough to remove the hardcoded phrase entries yet. The current transitive math is `enhances * 0.3`, `siblings * 0.15`, and `depends_on * 0.2`, with a floor of `0.1` before a boost is emitted (`.opencode/skills/skill-advisor/scripts/skill_advisor.py:98-119`). For `spec folder review`, the hardcoded primary boost is `2.0` to `sk-deep-review`, so the graph-derived `sk-code-review` boost would be `2.0 * 0.8 * 0.2 = 0.32`, which is much smaller than the explicit `0.8`. For `figma css`, the graph-derived `sk-code-web` boost would be `0.8 * 0.4 * 0.3 = 0.096`, which falls below the `0.1` cutoff and is dropped entirely. So the relationships exist in the graph, but one is only partially substitutable and the other is effectively inert.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/008-skill-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:11:4. `intent_signals` can already auto-generate a meaningful exact subset of the phrase table. I found 21 exact phrase-skill matches where the hardcoded phrase string is already present verbatim in a skill’s `intent_signals`. The cleanest exact duplicates are: `code review`, `pr review`, `security review`, and `quality gate` for `sk-code-review` (`.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/graph-metadata.json:19-20`); `deep research` and `research loop` for `sk-deep-research` (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/graph-metadata.json:15-16`); `deep review`, `review loop`, `iterative review`, and `spec folder review` for `sk-deep-review` (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/graph-metadata.json:17-18`); `semantic search`, `code search`, and `coco index` for `mcp-coco-index` (`.opencode/skills/mcp-coco-index/graph-metadata.json:13-14`); `improve agent` and `evaluate agent` for `sk-improve-agent`; and the exact CLI phrases `gemini cli`, `delegate to gemini`, `codex cli`, `delegate to codex`, `copilot cli`, and `delegate to copilot` from their respective metadata.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/008-skill-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:9:5. `sk-deep-review` is mostly accurate on its explicit review-loop ties, but it still lacks a graph connection to the spec-validation system it routinely works alongside. The metadata correctly records `depends_on -> sk-code-review` and `siblings -> sk-deep-research` (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/graph-metadata.json:7-13`). However, its intent signals include `spec folder review` (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/graph-metadata.json:17-18`), while `system-spec-kit` owns spec-folder/validation/context routing (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:3`, `.opencode/skills/skill-advisor/scripts/skill_advisor.py:919-927`). That coupling is visible in routing behavior but absent from the graph.
./.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/008-skill-advisor/001-skill-advisor-graph/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:13:- High confidence: add a graph relationship between `system-spec-kit` and `sk-deep-review`. Best current fit looks like `system-spec-kit -> enhances -> sk-deep-review` because spec-folder context and validation increase deep-review usefulness, but the direction should be confirmed before editing metadata.
